<TITLE> Shipping ministry assesses its ADP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 30 (bdnews24.com) -- Shipping minister Shajahan Khan on Wednesday asked the ministry officials to complete all the tender process of development projects by January. The minister gave the order at a meeting called to assess the ADP implementation of the shipping ministry and its affiliated agencies. The meeting was informed that in 2009-10 fiscal year, the ministry-affiliated agencies implemented 15 projects under annual development programme (ADP) at a cost of Tk 159.83 crore and another five projects at a cost of Tk 248.11 crore from their own funds. It was told that the planning commission approved a block allocation of Tk 290 crore as per the requirement of the ministry. The meeting, among other things, discussed demolition of illegal structures on the banks of the Buriganga river, solution to garbage pollution, and collection of more rescue water vessels. It was told that removal of polythene garbage from the bed of Buriganga would begin on January 6. Shipping ministry joint secretary (administration) Mohammad Alauddin, BIWTA chairman Abdul Malek Mia and other senior officials of the ministry and agencies concerned attended the meeting. bdn
